  "body": "\n### Description\n\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\n*Type*: Bug\n\n*Summary*: only on iOS: user can't open 1:1 chat because of `error No matching clause:offline`, after closing the popup app is not usable as it shows empty white screen, so relaunch is needed. After this 1:1 chat can't be opened again even if app is online. \n\nAssumption: To get the error user needs to move app on background and back while being offline but it's possible that issue happens in more cases\n\n\nSee exact steps below\n\n\n\n#### Expected behavior\n\ncan open 1:1 chat and send/get messages\n\n#### Actual behavior\n\n\"error No matching clause:offline\"\n![81985](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6584810/63604946-3df5d780-c5cd-11e9-80b9-026d03aa883a.jpg)\n\n\n### Reproduction\n\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\nvideo: https://drive.google.com/open?id=1J7SSLQ8b25dFPE1yD6I4T0Vq1Hl9u-aX\n- Install Status\n- Create new account\n- select \"maybe later\" for both fingerprint and notifications\n- add new contact by scanning its qr code (1:1 chat is opened, use Add to contacts link in the chat)\n- send 1 text message in 1:1 chat\n- close app\n- launch app again\n- tap \"save password\" and sign in\n- Tap on \"Allow\" to allow notifications\n- open 1:1 chat\n- turn on Airplane mode, wait for \"Offline\" line to be shown in the app\n- move app on background and back\n- if no error shown then tap on Back to go to Chats and back to 1:1 chat \n- if no error shown try to move app to background couple of move times (also can scan another QR code with contact code to open new 1:1 chat)\n\n\n### Additional Information\n\n[comment]: # (Please do your best to fill this out.)\n- Status version: nightly from Aug 23 https://ci.status.im/job/status-react/job/nightly/1223/\n- Operating System:  iOS only: real iphone 6s iOS 12.4 and real iphone 7+ ios 12.3.1\n\n\n#### Logs\n\n[status_logs (5).zip](https://github.com/status-im/status-react/files/3535216/status_logs.5.zip)",
